This church has an Italian-style painted dome representing the prophet Elijah on a chariot and a chapel entirely painted with Flemish inspiration. You can also discover the crypt housing the tomb of Frederic Ozanam and the bones of the priests massacred in the courtyard of the church in September 1792. Free guided tour every Saturday except in August by volunteers.

This church is Cultural Heritage of Paris. Built in the 17th century for the barefoot Carmelites who arrived in Paris. In September 1792, during the French Revolution, more than 100 Carmelites were murdered in the garden.
